data.output: It was a rainy, dreary kind of day but just a normal one in England. I had a car full of petrol and I decided to take a drive out to the shopping centre; being outside today was not an option! As I was going round the bend just down the road, my car slipped on some spilt diesel. I went to pump my brakes but I ended up spinning out of control and crashed! Luckily I was not hurt so a day at home watching movies seemed the safer option.

My daughter was in a bad mood. She is a Leo star sign down to the letter! She will stamp her foot and huff and puff in the mornings when she does not want to wake up. I decided today was not the day to try and reason with her and the best thing to do was to send her back to bed until she felt better.

I walked into the musical hall, listening to an old woman playing the organ. I can't believe that I am now in charge of an empire, I don't know how I got into this position. Even though I am suppposedly in power I have been given so many rules I have to comply with. I feel like breaking all the rules and running away from here.

I woke up this morning feeling the gloom of a Monday morning. Why do Monday's have to exist? I suppose Tuesdays would just become the next Monday's wouldn't they! I would give any kind of payment right now just to stay in bed and not have to go to work.
